The paper proposes a generative model for drug discovery, which involves learning to sample molecules that satisfy multiple property constraints. This task involves graph generative models and composition of molecules from substructures. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science). The paper also involves image analysis and natural language processing techniques, which could place it in categories such as cs.CV (Computer Vision) and cs.CL (Computation and Language).
